        {
            "title": "Historical Background and Evolution of Graphic Design",
            "content": "The history of graphic design is rich and varied, tracing back to the origins of visual communication. Early forms of graphic design can be seen in ancient cave paintings and hieroglyphics, where visuals were used to convey stories and information. The invention of the printing press in the 15th century marked a significant milestone, as it allowed for the mass production of printed materials, leading to the development of typography and layout design. The 19th century saw the rise of advertising and the need for more sophisticated design techniques. The Bauhaus movement in the early 20th century played a pivotal role in shaping modern graphic design, emphasizing the integration of art, craft, and technology. With the advent of digital technology in the late 20th century, graphic design underwent another transformation, expanding into digital media and interactive design. Today, graphic design continues to evolve, incorporating new technologies such as virtual reality and augmented reality, while maintaining its foundational principles.",
            "relevance_score": 0.85
        },
        {
            "title": "The Role of Graphic Design in Branding and Marketing",
